<br>
Every man and woman in the US Military is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>*thoroughly*</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> trained and equipped for survival in a NBC environment.  I can vouch for this personally.  From the first weeks they enter the military until the end of their careers the are trained to deal with it.  And you'd better believe that they are undergoing heavy reinforcement and advanced training as we speak.  It would be foolish to think that the military has not taken this into consideration and is not preparing its people accordingly.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I ask you, would you be willing to go down to Iraq and go up against chemical/bio weapons to free the Iraqi people? Would you personally be willing to make that sacrifice for a foreign/alien people?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
