Come now Dark, you are smarter than this.  First of all, you are being misleading.  There is a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>possibility</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> (in my opinion, a remote one) that our troops will be &quot;going up against chemical/bio weapons&quot;.  You make it sound as though it is a certainty.  It is not.<br>
<br>
I swear to you I am not trying to be insulting...having read your other posts in this thread I have a lot of respect for you.  Nonetheless, I believe that people think like you do on this particular issue because they have not experienced firsthand the absolute devastation that our military is capable of inflicting, nor do they understand the mindset of its members.  I have, and I do.  Would your average citizen want to go off to war?  No.  Are our military members ready and willing?  You bet your ass.<br>
<br>
As I've said before, I was in the Army for four years and am still in a position to be called to active duty should it become necessary (which it will not).  I would go tomorrow if they called me tonight.  No question in my mind.  The people that sign up for the military know full well, as I did, that things like this can happen.  It is the entire reason for the existence of the military, afterall.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Saddam Hussein will retreat into the cities and pursue a urban gurilla warfare agenda which will leave us unable to carpet bomb the cities for &quot;political reasons&quot;, forcing us to send in ground troops to take/occupy the cities.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Do you think so?  Do you really think his people will shelter him?  I'm not contradicting you because I don't fully understand the Iraqi people or their way of thinking.  This is purely opinion.  But I cannot imagine that they really enjoy being ruled with an iron fist by Saddam Hussein.  Iraqi soldiers were surrendering to us in DROVES during the Gulf War.  Remember, they were being held in their positions quite literally at gunpoint.<br>
<br>
Finally they just said &quot;screw you&quot; and came out waving white flags.  To me that does not indicate an Army that is faithful to its leader.  Would a faithful Army have to be held in position by its own policing force?  Absolutely not.  And since the army was virtually all conscripted, it does not indicate a populace that is loyal to its &quot;president&quot;.  Not to me, anyway.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If this happens, America faces the very real possibility of another Vietnam war with gurilla warfare and all...are you willing to see the body bags come home?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No it doesn't.  Don't buy into that BS.  This is nothing more than a favorite scare tactic that originates with &quot;anti-war movement&quot;.  It is so pathetically tired.  They've been trying to conjure up visions of some kind of Veitnam-like nightmare scenario for every military action for the last 30 years.  And the sad thing is that it is the same group of people that led the peace movement in the US in the 60's.  You know, the same filth that covered US Soldiers coming home from Vietnam in pig's blood (and worse).  The &quot;make love not war&quot; crowd.  The &quot;sex, drugs and rock-and-roll&quot; crowd.  Hippies, in other words.  They feel they need to justify their beliefs and their pathetic existances for the past 35 years to themselves, and I guess I can't blame them for that.  I dont find it any less infuriating though.<br>
<br>
They said the same thing about Grenada, Panama, the first Gulf War, Bosnia, Kosovo...you get the idea.  It didn't happen in those instances and it will not happen in this one.  If you don't think that we've learned from Vietnam and moved on accordingly you are very mistaken.  It will not happen because we will not allow it to happen.  Anti-war types would really love for you to believe that we're in for a prolonged guerilla war of some type.  Give me a break.  There is so much misinformation like this flying around out there it is really sad.  Please look a little deeper before you buy into it.  Don't be another Belarkan and jump on every anti-US/anti-war bandwagon that comes along because it is currently the cool thing to do.<br>
